SQL> /*******
DOC>
DOC>Before you run this script you should replace the following
DOC>tokens using sed.
DOC>
DOC>Create a file called dev.sed (or test.sed or prod.sed) containing:
DOC>
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_BIGIND_TS,/foo/bar/bigind.dbs,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_TINYIND_TS,/foo/bar/tinyind.dbs,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_BIGTAB_TS,/foo/bar/bigtab.dbs,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_TINYTAB_TS,/foo/bar/tinytab.dbs,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_BIGIND_SIZE,1024M,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_TINYIND_SIZE,12M,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_BIGTAB_SIZE,1024M,g
DOC>1,$s,PARAM_TINYTAB_SIZE,12M,g
DOC>
DOC>Then create your *real* script by entering:
DOC>
DOC>sed -f dev.sed < shamu_ddl.sql > shamu_dev.sql
DOC>
DOC>PARAM_BIGIND_TS - Name of First Big Index Tablespace File
DOC>PARAM_TINYIND_TS - Name of First Tiny Index Tablespace File
DOC>PARAM_BIGTAB_TS - Name of First Big table Tablespace File
DOC>PARAM_TINYTAB_TS - Name of First Tiny Table Tablespace File
DOC>
DOC>Adding additional data files where needed comes under the jurisdiction of the DBA group.
DOC>
DOC>PARAM_BIGIND_SIZE - Size of First Big Index Tablespace File
DOC>PARAM_TINYIND_SIZE - Size of First Tiny Index Tablespace File
DOC>PARAM_BIGTAB_SIZE - Size of First Big table Tablespace File
DOC>PARAM_TINYTAB_SIZE - Size of First Tiny Table Tablespace File
DOC>
DOC>
DOC>********/
SQL> 
SQL> 
SQL> pause

